<br>
Now, why shouldn't a critical hit double that increased base damage again? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/urunkledarokk.showPublicProfile?language=EN>RunkleDaRokk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 24<br> <font color=#333399>(6/19/02 11:23:10 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=27650.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Spell Casting Fury Crit Damage Cap?</span><hr size=1> I had a 2400 crit with mage focus damage bracer i think it is, and my fury is only level 2, i had no damage 3 items on <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/useriena.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Seriena</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 408<br> <font color=#333399>(6/19/02 11:36:49 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=27650.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Spell Casting Fury Crit Damage Cap?</span><hr size=1> No, it doesn't increase your base dmg. Your base is still 1024 anything after that varies. <p><br><br><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=117440" TARGET="_NEW">Seriena,</A> 60 druid<br>
