<br>
Regardless of nomenclature, it's a matter of concept.  <br>
<br>
A damage focus item does what?  It randomly increases the damage by a small amount each and every time you cast the spell.   (It is, functionally, the inverse of the random resistance effect.) <br>
<br>
In contrast, a critical hit doesn't affect every spell cast.  Instead, there is a small chance that that particular cast may be a critical strike, doing up to double the damage it would otherwise have done.  <br>
<br>
And what is the damage it would otherwise have done if there were not critical strike?  The damage including the focus effect, of course.  <br>
<br>
Again, why shouldn't the focus effect increase be included in a critical strike calculation? <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uscirocco.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Scirocco</A> at: 6/19/02 11:47:49 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uaaeamdar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aaeamdar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 178<br> <font color=#333399>(6/19/02 11:59:55 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=27650.topic&index=6>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Spell Casting Fury Crit Damage Cap?</span><hr size=1> Personally I am not so interested in the philosophy of it as I am in the answer.  (No offense to anyone, but I would like to see this thread be about a meaningful answer to the question, rather than a debate on the way the game <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  should</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> work.)<br>
